    @ModelExternalEvents(imported={SwitchOnHeater.class,SwitchOffHeater.class,Heat.class,DoNotHeat.class})
 @ModelExportedVariable(name="currentIntensity",
                       type=java.lang.Double.class)
public class HeaterElectricityModel
extends fr.sorbonne_u.devs_simulation.hioa.models.AtomicHIOA
    The class HeaterElectricityModel defines a simulation model for the electricity consumption of the heater.

    Description

    The model is a simple state-based one: the electricity consumption is assumed to be constant in each possible state of the heater (State.OFF => 0.0, State.ON => NOT_HEATING_POWER and State.HEATING => HEATING_POWER). The state of the heater is modified by the reception of external events (SwitchOnHeater, SwitchOffHeater, Heat and DoNotHeat). The electricity consumption is stored in the exported variable currentIntensity.

    Initially, the mode is in state State.OFF and the electricity consumption at 0.0.

    Invariant

     invariant       NOT_HEATING_POWER >= 0.0
 invariant       HEATING_POWER > NOT_HEATING_POWER
 invariant       TENSION > 0.0

    Created on : 2021-09-20

    Author:
    Jacques Malenfant
